        private boolean checkColumnMetaData(java.sql.ResultSet rs,
                          java.util.List<Table.ColumnMetaDatum> metaData)
                             throws java.sql.SQLException
        Checks whether the given ResultSet corresponds to the given column metadata. The ResultSet should be retrieved from the getColumns method of a DatabaseMetaData object, and its cursor should be positioned before the first row.
        Parameters:
        rs - The ResultSet that shall be checked to see if it corresponds to the column metadata.
        metaData - The column metadata that shall be checked to see if it corresponds to the ResultSet.
        Returns:
